sections.content:
“Federal  Lands  Commissioner”  means  the  Federal  Lands 
Commissioner  appointed  under  the  Federal  Lands  Commissioner 
Act  1957 [Act  349];

“infectious  or  contagious  disease”  means  any  disease  declared 
to   be   infectious   or   contagious   by   regulations   made   under 
section  88;

“Minister”  means  the  Minister  for  the  time  being  charged  with 
the responsibility  for  railways in Sabah, Sarawak and the Federal 
Territory of Labuan;

(a)  all  rails,  beams,  cables,  sidings,  or  branches  worked 
over  for  the   purposes  of,  or  in  connection  with,  a 
railway;

“railway  company”  includes  any  person  or  persons,  whether 
incorporated  or  not,  who  are  owners  or  lessees  of  a  railway  or 
parties  to  an  agreement  for  working  a  railway;

“railway  official”  means  any  person  employed  by  or  on  behalf 
of  any  railway  company  to  perform  any  function  in  connection 
with  a  railway;

“rolling-stock”  includes  tenders,  motors,  coaches,  wagons,  trucks, 
trolleys,  carriages  of  any  kind  and  locomotive  and  other  kinds  of 
engine used on a  railway;

or 
narrowing  of any  public  road,  navigable  river, 
canal or railway;

(a)  approve  the  application  and  issue  a  licence  to  the 
applicant on  payment  of  such  fees  as  he  thinks  fit; 
or

(a)   the forms of the notices mentioned in section 45, and 
the particulars  of  the  accident  which  those  notices  
are  to contain;

(b)    takes  up,  removes,  loosens,  or  displaces  any  rail, 
sleeper  or  other    matter  or  thing  appertaining  to  a 
railway;

(a)    take  temporary  possession  of  any  railway  or  railway 
service  or  facility  established,  maintained  or  worked 
by a railway company;

(d)    to  prescribe  maximum  charges  to  be  paid  for  the 
conveyance of  passengers  and  goods  by  any  railway 
company;

(f)    to  regulate  the  construction  and  maintenance  of 
railways and  the crossing  or  manner  of  approach  to 
any  public road  or  thoroughfare  by  a  train;

(h)    to  provide  for  the  preservation  and  promotion  of 
good  order,    sanitation  and  cleanliness  upon  a 
railway;

development  or 
redevelopment of any railway infrastructure or facilities; 
and

(a)    such  sums  as  may  be  provided  by  the  Federal 
Government from  time  to  time  for  the  purposes  of 
the  Corporation under  this  Part;

any  other  offence  punishable  with  imprisonment  (in 
itself  only  or  in  addition  to  or  in  lieu  to  a  fine)  for 
more than  two  years;
